The paper focuses on scene parsing with deep learning, which is a computer vision task, indicating that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. The paper also introduces a new context aggregation strategy, which involves computing similarities and aggregating features, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper deals with semantic segmentation, which involves natural language processing, indicating that it may also belong to the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. Finally, the paper uses state-of-the-art performance on three semantic segmentation benchmarks, suggesting that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
